title: Taiwan Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Taiwan Three Month Interbank Rate increased to 1.19 percent on Wednesday November 9 from 1.18 percent in the previous day. Interbank Rate in Taiwan averaged 0.94 percent from 2005 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 2.37 percent in June of 2007 and a record low of 0.47 percent in March of 2020. In Taiwan, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Taiwan Two to Six Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: DGBAS, Taiwan
